vectorData.altText: LOOK at the lateral aspect of the
mediastinum on both sides of your cadaver,  keeping these anatomical relationships in mind, and find the phrenic nerves.

large forceps or your fingers, and gently ease the phrenic nerves free from the lateral aspect of the mediastinum. Observe their course to the dome of the diaphragm. Leave the phrenic nerves intact along their length, attached to the dome of the diaphragm.

You will be able to see them through the mediastinal parietal pleura; they will appear as thick white cords running anterior to the root of the lung. Confirm your identification with your TA before proceeding.
